# Motion Detection and Intrusion Detection System

This repository contains source code for a motion detection and intrusion detection system using a Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ and the HC-SR501 PIR sensor.

## Motion Detection

### motion_detector.c

This file contains a C program for Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ to detect motion using the HC-SR501 PIR sensor connected to GPIO 17, toggling an LED connected to GPIO 18; it includes error handling for GPIO initialization failures and a simple debounce mechanism.

### motion_detector_mqtt.c

This file contains a C program for Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ to detect motion using the HC-SR501 PIR sensor connected to GPIO 17, toggling an LED connected to GPIO 18; it includes error handling for GPIO initialization failures, a simple debounce mechanism, and sends motion detection events to a MQTT broker (e.g., Home Assistant) using the [mosquitto](https://mosquitto.org/) library.

## Intrusion Detection

### intrusion_detector.c

This file contains a C program for Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ to monitor the distance using a HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor (trigger on GPIO 23, echo on GPIO 24), activating a buzzer connected to GPIO 25 if the object is within 20cm, with error handling for sensor failures and a debounce mechanism.

### intrusion_detector_mqtt.c

This file contains a C program for Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ to monitor the distance using a HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor (trigger on GPIO 23, echo on GPIO 24), activating a buzzer connected to GPIO 25 if the object is within 20cm, with error handling for sensor failures, a debounce mechanism, and sends intrusion detection events to a MQTT broker (e.g., Home Assistant) using the [mosquitto](https://mosquitto.org/) library.

## Requirements

* Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+
* HC-SR501 PIR sensor (GPIO 17)
* HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor (trigger on GPIO 23, echo on GPIO 24)
* Buzzer (GPIO 25)
* WiringPi library (sudo apt-get install wiringpi)
* Mosquitto library (sudo apt-get install mosquitto mosquitto-lib)

## Installation

Install WiringPi using `sudo apt-get install wiringpi`.
Install Mosquitto using `sudo apt-get install mosquitto mosquitto-lib`.

## Usage

### Motion Detection

Run the motion detection program using:

```
sudo./motion_detector
```

### Motion Detection with MQTT

To enable MQTT support, update the MQTT_BROKER_ADDRESS constant in motion_detector_mqtt.c to the address of your MQTT broker.

Run the motion detection program with MQTT support using:

```
sudo./motion_detector_mqtt
```

### Intrusion Detection

Run the intrusion detection program using:

```
sudo./intrusion_detector
```

### Intrusion Detection with MQTT

To enable MQTT support, update the MQTT_BROKER_ADDRESS constant in intrusion_detector_mqtt.c to the address of your MQTT broker.

Run the intrusion detection program with MQTT support using:

```
sudo./intrusion_detector_mqtt
```

## Troubleshooting

### wiringPiSetup failed

Check that you have installed the wiringPi library and that it is configured correctly.

### wiringPiISR failed

Check that you have configured the GPIO pins correctly. Ensure that the PIR sensor is connected to a digital input pin (GPIO 17) and the buzzer is connected to a digital output pin (GPIO 18).

### MQTT disconnected unexpectedly with code

Check that you have configured the MQTT broker address and port correctly.
Ensure that the MQTT broker is running and listening for connections.

