# Raspberry Pi Motion Detection and Logging

A C program for Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+ to detect motion using a HC-SR501 PIR sensor connected to GPIO 17, logging timestamped events to "motion_log.txt" using `wiringPi`, with robust error handling on GPIO setup and file operations.

## Setup

- Install `wiringPi` using `sudo apt-get install wiringpi`.
- Compile `motion_detector.c` using `gcc -o motion_detector motion_detector.c -lpigpio`.
- Run the program with `sudo./motion_detector`.

## Usage

The program detects motion events by polling the GPIO pin connected to the PIR sensor. When motion is detected, it logs the timestamp of the event to the file "motion_log.txt". The program uses a pull-down resistor to reduce noise and prevent false positives.

## Acknowledgements

- `pigpio` library: https://github.hcom/jimh/pigpio

